The Project

VentureCrowd Trust No. 0666 (Riverview) (Fund) has been established to provide funding for the acquisition of a residential development project located at 1 & 19 McEwan Street, Riverview QLD 4303.

Ipswich City Council granted the Property Development Approval for 115 townhomes and 3 retail tenancies with 4 apartments above on the 19th of November 2018. The purchase price of the property is $5,697,800.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
The Location

Just 28 minutes from the Brisbane CBD, Riverview is in Ipswich City Council. The Property is close to several schools which include Ipswich Grammar School, Riverview Primary School, St Peter Claver College, Collingwood Park State School and Redbank State School. The property is close to the Ipswich Motorway, Cunningham Highway and the Warrego Highway, which will make this development an accessible destination.

The Riverview train station is only a short 200m or a 3-minute walk from the development site. Besides the train station, other major transport facilities include the Moggill Ferry, which is situated less than 1 kilometre away.

Other notable landmarks nearby include TAFE QLD and Costco, which are in the neighbouring suburb of Bundamba. The property is also close to Redbank Plaza and Greater Springfieldâ€™s Orion precinct, both 10 minutes away.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Market Drivers*

With over 7000 people moving to the area in the past year, Ipswich is the fourth fastest-growing municipality in Australia. It continues to be attractive to young families seeking residential properties because of its accessibility to Brisbane, Toowoomba and Warwick, and many amenities within armâ€™s reach.

Across the Greater Ipswich region, approximately $15.3 billion worth of major transport and infrastructure improvements are either underway, proposed or have been recently completed. The western corridor, which Riverview is part of, attracts 85% of Ipswichâ€™s total population growth with major infrastructure developments in Greater Springfield including a new 1200-bed private Mater hospital, and Greater Springfieldâ€™s Parkside business precinct. Nearby Amberley Air Force Base employs over 5,000 people (uniform and civilian).

Despite higher than average rental demand (49.6%) in Riverview, there are currently no rental vacancies. Median rentals have increased by an average of $70 per week in the Western Corridor and rental yields are 5.6%, higher than the regionâ€™s 4.8% average. Residential property sales in Riverview increased by a staggering 44% last financial year and the area is seeing an influx of young, wealthier families.

*Broad Property Research & Advisory.

The Olympics Factor*

The 2032 Brisbane Olympics is forecast to inject $8.1 billion into the Queensland economy, generate 100,000 new local jobs and inject $17.6 billion into the wider Australian economy with billions in increased export opportunities and international tourism expenditure to follow. $700 billion will be spent on infrastructure projects in the region, including building new venues and upgrading existing ones, building new athlete villages in Brisbane, the Gold Coast and the Sunshine Coast; and upgrading road and rail networks linking the SEQ locations that will be venues for Olympic sports.

With this level of extra funding for major city-building projects, South East Queensland will be an even more attractive place to live, work and play, creating a ripple effect throughout the local economy, which is expected to drive housing demand and property values.

* According to KPMG projections

Financial Forecast

The project is forecasting total development costs of $53,445,693 and net sale proceeds of $60,233,273. This results in a development profit of $6,787,580 and a project margin of 12.7%.

The Fund

The Fund is an unregistered wholesale managed investment scheme, structured as a unit trust, the trustee of which is VentureCrowd Nominees Pty Ltd (ACN 166 599 140).

Investors will acquire B Class Units in the Fund at an issue price of $1.00 per Unit.

The Fund will acquire preference shares issued by Riverview Qld Development Pty Ltd (ACN 659 873 891) (SPV).

The Trustee will issue Units to investors in its capacity as an authorised representative of VentureCrowd Pty Ltd (ACN 166 598 849) under its Australian Financial Services License No.503381.

Funds will be used for:

  • Civil works
  • Dwelling construction

With a minimum investment of $10,000, wholesale and pre-approved investors can invest at $1 per Unit.

Key investment highlights include:

Prospective investors should review and seek independent legal advice regarding the Trust Deed before applying to invest in the Fund. The Trust Deed is available on request.

Who Can Invest?
This offer is open to wholesale and pre-approved investors. If you have a wholesale investor certification, have assets of AUD$2.5 million or have a gross income of the last two financial years of at least AUD$250,000 per annum, this may apply to you. If you are an experienced investor with multiple investments in venture capital or property, you may be qualified by our team as a wholesale investor upon reviewing your documentation.

Fees and Expenses

The fees and expenses payable in connection with the management of the Fund are as follows:

  • Contribution Fee: 1.1% of your investment amount in the Fund, payable upon acceptance of your investment by the Trustee
  • Management Fee: 1.65% p.a. of the Gross Asset Value of the Fund, payable by the Fundâ€™s assets
  • Expenses: estimated at 0.5% p.a. of the Gross Asset Value of the Fund, payable by the Fundâ€™s assets
  • Transfer Fee (if you wish to transfer your holding to someone else): $500 + 2% of the total amount transferred (payable by the unit holder initiating transfer)*

*If you identify the buyer in advance, the 2% fee does not apply. VentureCrowd cannot guarantee a purchaser for your holding.

Risks

Whilst the directors of the Fund Manager are experienced investment managers and the senior executives of the Development Manager have substantial experience in managing property development projects, there are always risks associated with development and construction which may, either directly or indirectly, result in reduced distributions and/or a loss of some of the capital value of an investment in the Fund.

Before deciding whether to subscribe for Units, you should consider whether an investment in this Fund, the underlying asset of which will be the Property, is suitable for you. If you are in doubt as to whether you should invest, please consult a suitably qualified professional advisor.

The key risks associated with investing in the Fund are set out in the Information Memorandum attached below and include the following:

  • a downturn in the general economic and market conditions in South-East Queensland;
  • unfavourable movements in interest rates, inflation or the unemployment rate;
  • changes to the law (including tax laws) and accounting rules;
  • industrial relations disputes and strikes;
  • natural disasters, including earthquakes, fire and storm;
  • social unrest, terrorist attack or war in Australia or overseas;
  • no guarantee of performance or return;
  • development costs and project expenditure being lower than forecast;
  • issues and delays with council;
  • related parties not performing; and
  • availability of construction funding.
